---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — QA Learning"
  description="What data QA Learning collects, why, how long it is kept, and how to request deletion."
>
  <main id="main" class="privacy-page">
    <article class="prose privacy-prose">
      <span class="eyebrow">legal</span>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="privacy-meta">Last updated: <time datetime="2026-05-31">31 May 2026</time></p>

      <p>
        QA Learning is a personal portfolio and study site. This policy explains what personal data is
        collected when you use the site, why it is collected, how long it is kept, and how you can
        request deletion.
      </p>

      <h2>Data collected</h2>
      <p>When you sign in with GitHub or Google, the following data is stored:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Name</strong> — as provided by your OAuth provider.</li>
        <li><strong>Email address</strong> — used to link GitHub and Google accounts that share the
          same verified email.</li>
        <li><strong>Avatar URL</strong> — the profile picture URL from your OAuth provider.</li>
        <li><strong>GitHub username</strong> (<code>githubHandle</code>) — stored when you sign in
          with GitHub.</li>
        <li><strong>Session cookie</strong> — a signed, HttpOnly cookie that keeps you authenticated
          between visits. It expires after a multi-day period and is refreshed on activity.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Activity data is also stored against your account: quiz attempts and scores, lesson completion
        marks, exam session results, spaced-repetition card grades, and a daily-activity heatmap.
      </p>
      <p>No passwords are stored. Email-and-password sign-in is disabled.</p>

      <h2>Why data is collected</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>To persist your learning progress (lesson completion, quiz history, streak).</li>
        <li>To power spaced-repetition reviews tied to your account.</li>
        <li>To link GitHub and Google sign-ins that share a verified email, avoiding duplicate
          accounts.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        The session cookie is strictly necessary for the authenticated features above.
        No marketing cookies, third-party tracking pixels, or advertising are used.
      </p>

      <h2>Retention</h2>
      <p>
        Account and activity data is kept for as long as your account exists.
        Session cookies expire after their configured lifetime (typically 7–30 days of
        inactivity) and are not re-issued after sign-out.
      </p>

      <h2>Third parties</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Party</th>
            <th>Role</th>
            <th>What they receive</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>GitHub</strong></td>
            <td>OAuth provider</td>
            <td>OAuth flow only; GitHub receives the OAuth callback. Profile data (name, email,
              avatar, username) is fetched from GitHub's API at sign-in and stored locally.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Google</strong></td>
            <td>OAuth provider</td>
            <td>OAuth flow only; Google receives the OAuth callback. Profile data (name, email,
              avatar) is fetched from Google's API at sign-in and stored locally.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Neon</strong></td>
            <td>Postgres database host</td>
            <td>All account and activity data is stored in a Neon serverless Postgres database.
              Neon operates under its own
              <a href="https://neon.tech/privacy-policy" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">privacy policy</a>.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Vercel</strong></td>
            <td>Hosting and edge runtime</td>
            <td>Requests are served via Vercel. Vercel may collect standard server logs (IP address,
              user-agent, timestamp) per its
              <a href="https://vercel.com/legal/privacy-policy" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">privacy policy</a>.
              Vercel Analytics (aggregate, cookie-free) and Speed Insights are enabled.</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2>Account deletion</h2>
      <p>
        There is currently no self-serve account-deletion button in the UI. To request deletion of
        your account and all associated data (profile, quiz attempts, lesson completions, exam
        sessions, spaced-repetition cards, activity history), send an email to:
      </p>
      <p>
        <a href="mailto:byk.plai@gmail.com" class="privacy-contact">byk.plai@gmail.com</a>
      </p>
      <p>
        Include the email address linked to your account. Deletion will be completed within
        <strong>30 days</strong> of the request.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For any privacy questions or concerns, contact
        <a href="mailto:byk.plai@gmail.com">byk.plai@gmail.com</a>.
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .privacy-page {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 48px 40px 64px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .privacy-page {
      padding: 32px 20px 48px;
    }
  }

  .privacy-prose h1 {
    margin: 8px 0 4px;
  }

  .privacy-meta {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--ink-3);
    margin: 0 0 2em;
  }

  .privacy-contact {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 15px;
  }
</style>
